By you, like the sea upon the earth,
Never to mix, yet touch brings mirth.

By you, like the moon upon the sunlight,
At a distance, yet intertwined in its spite.

By you, like the two upon a ballroom,
Only we can decypher this neume

And by the edge of the night,
Together, in a prelude of fright
My hands tremble, a raise in my hair,
A leap of faith, and a landing there,
Inching closer, a natural possession,
As two melt, crave, and indulge in obsession.

By you, I am enchanted